me after seeing it: I have never hated any villain so much in my life I want to see it die in the first two seconds of CM2
summary:
I know the predatory and abusive way the Supreme Intelligence treats Yon-Rogg is already 
gut-wrenching

and disgusting enough...
body:
I know the predatory and abusive way the Supreme Intelligence treats Yon-Rogg is already gut-wrenching and disgusting enough on its own but I want to highlight two more things to show even more how fucked up it is.

Number one: Yon-Rogg sees himself yet the Intelligence is taller and therefore more intimidating, further portraying the immense power imbalance.

You could think that this is just the way the SI presents itself (since it also changes the eye and hair color) but the height of Mar-Vell stays exactly the same.

Number two: Notice how much darker the simulation is for Yon-Rogg? Even when Carol became their enemy it’s still not as dark as it is for their loyal subordinate.

I don’t want to know how many years Yon-Rogg has suffered through this (especially considering that as a commander, the leader of the Starforce and Vers’ mentor he had to talk to them even more than the others) and I really don’t want to know how bad it has gotten at times (not to mention what happened when he returned to Hala) but I truly hope we get to see this thing burn in the next film - and it would be great if Yon could stand-up-against his abuser to help Carol defeat them, he deserves that closure.
